benefits and challenges of building relationships, dialogues, and perspectives that extend beyond the boundaries of nation-states and disciplines. The contributors open a dialogue between feminist theorists and scholars of social movements in other disciplines in order to foster mutual recognition of common interests and identities. Although feminists and women's groups face challenges as they build solidarities beyond borders, this book makes the case that these links can be extended to embrace other progressive movements and their goals.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Gender Studies.2bisacsh1 aAlba, Carmen L. Díaz, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeaulieu, Elsa, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaouette, Dominique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCaouette, Dominique, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aConway, Janet, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDufou, Pascale, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDufour, Pascale, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aDufour, Pascale, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEstrada-Claudio, Sylvia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLopreite, Débora, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLyons, Lenore, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMasson, Dominique, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMasson, Dominique, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMatt, Diane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe Gru